{% set mainAccount = entity.field_account_reference.entity %}
{% set mainContact = additional_vars.primary_contact %}

<body>
<div class="container">
  <div class="header proposal-row">
    <table>
      <tr>
        <td><img src="/themes/gary/logo.png" height="100px" width="100px"></td>
        <td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
        <td style="width: 8cm;">
          <p>Evergreen Certified LLC</p>
          <p>502 Rainier Ave S – Suite 206</p>
          <p>Seattle WA 98144</p>
          <p>www.evergreencertified.com</p>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table>
  </div>
  <br>
  <div class="date proposal-row">
    <p><span class="label">Date: </span>{{ "now"|date("m/d/Y") }} - Proposal Valid for 30 Days</p>
  </div>
  <br>
  <div class="account-info proposal-row">
    <h3>Account information</h3>
    <div class="account-info-table-container">
      <table class="account-info-table table">
        <tr><td>Account: </td><td>{{ entity.field_orig_account.entity.title.value  }}</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Contact Name: </td><td>{{ additional_vars.primary_contact.title.value }}</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Email: </td><td>{{ additional_vars.primary_contact.field_contact_email.value|default(entity.field_account_reference.entity.field_billing_email.value)  }}</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Phone: </td><td>{{ additional_vars.primary_contact.field_contact_phone.value|default(entity.field_account_reference.entity.field_phone.value) }}</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Billing Account: </td><td>{{ entity.field_account_reference.entity.title.value  }}</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Street Address: </td><td>{{ entity.field_account_reference.entity.field__billing_address.value }}</td></tr>
        <tr><td>City, St, Zip</td><td>{{ entity.field_account_reference.entity.field__billing_city.value }}, {{ entity.field_account_reference.entity.field__billing_state.value }}, {{ entity.field_account_reference.entity.field_billing_zip.value }}</td></tr>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
  <br>
  <div class="project-info proposal-row">
    <h3>Project Information</h3>
    <div class="project-info-table-container">
      <table class="project-info-table table">
        <tr><td>Project Description: </td><td>{{ entity.field_description.value }}</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Street Address: </td><td>{{ entity.field_address.value }}</td></tr>
        <tr><td>City, St, Zip</td><td>{{ entity.field_city.value }}, {{ entity.field_state.value|upper }}, {{ entity.field_zip.value }}</td></tr>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
  <br>
  <br>
  <div class="proposed-services proposal-row">
    <h3>Proposed Services</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>National Green Building Standard (NGBS) Verification – Multifamily</li>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Setup & Coordination:</strong>Includes coordinating with NGBS to register project, confirmation of NGBS enrollment, and coordination with the builder about key project milestones and submittals.</li>
        <li><strong>Game Planning Meeting: </strong>An initial 1.5-hour meeting to review project goals and highlight the certification requirements with the builder’s team.</li>
        <li><strong>Support: </strong>Ongoing verifier consulting and support to help meet the project goals.</li>
        <li><strong>Site Visits: </strong>On site verification of NGBS credits at the following phases of construction: Air-Sealing, Insulation, and Project Completion. NGBS requires that all units be inspection, which could require additional multiple site visits at all phases depending on construction timeline.</li>
        <li><strong>Final Reporting:</strong>Preparation of required verifier report for NGBS. Includes photo documentation, compilation of builder submittals/receipts, and final review of the NGBS scoring checklists. REQUIRES documentation that will be provided by the builder.</li>
      </ol>
    </ol>
  </div>
  <div class="pagebreak"></div>
  <div class="fees proposal-row">
    <h3>Fees</h3>
    <table class="fees-table">
      <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Description</th>
        <th>Rate</th>
        <th>Qty</th>
        <th>Total</th>
      </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
      {% for service in entity.field_opportunity_services_ref.referencedEntities %}
        <tr>
          <td>{{ service.field_opportunity_service.entity.title.value }}</td>
          <td>${{ service.field_service_amount.value|number_format }}</td>
          <td>{{ service.field_quantity.value }}</td>
          <td style="width: 2cm">${{ service.field_line_total.value|number_format }}</td>
        </tr>
      {% endfor %}
      <tr>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Total Fees</strong></td>
        <td></td>
        <td></td>
        <td style="width: 2cm">${{ entity.field_amount.value|number_format }}</td>
      </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <br>
    <table class="fees-table">
      <tr>
        <td>20% Initial payment at start of work. Will be credited toward final total.</td>
        <td style="width: 2cm">${{ (entity.field_amount.value * 0.2)|number_format }}</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
  </div>
  <br>
  <div class="proposal-row">
    <h3>Payment Schedule</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>20% initial payment required to commence work and remaining balance at final.</strong> Final invoice will be issued after final site visit. Payment must be received prior to our submittal of final verification notices and report to NGBS.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="proposal-row">
    <h3>Builder Documentation Requirements</h3>
    <p>Receipts and documentation are REQUIRED for NGBS certification. The builder must submit required documentation to Evergreen Certified prior to final checklist being submitted to the National Green Building Standard staff. Evergreen Certified will provide a list of required documents based on the project checklist approved by the Builder. The following are select examples of required documentation.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Faucets, toilets and showerheads specifications or receipts</li>
      <li>Flooring, cabinet, and carpet invoices</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="proposal-row">
    <h3>Limitations</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Evergreen Certified can only confirm points/credits related to the National Green Building Standard (NGBS) Scoring Tool. Evergreen Certified assumes no liability for failure of a project to qualify for Certification as a result of the Builder’s performance with respect to NGBS’s requirements and submittal of qualifying documentation. Evergreen Certified will not and does not confirm any compliance with energy code or building permit requirements.</li>
      <li>The proposed services and fees do not include membership or project enrollment fees charged by Home Innovation’s National Green Building Standard. Payment must be made directly to them for project enrollment fees. Amounts vary according to project type and will be billed directly by Home Innovation’s National Green Building Standard staff.</li>
      <li>Evergreen Certified does not warrant the performance of building systems or the construction methods used to meet certification requirements. Evergreen Certified assumes no liability for costs associated with building performance.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
